content:
Service Cloud View the Sentiments of a Call Conversation

After a call ends, view the customer and agent sentiments in the Call Audio Player. Each utterance can have a positive, negative, or neutral sentiment. To identify what was said when negative sentiments occur, play the recording at those moments. An agent can then follow up with the customer to turn a negative experience into a positive one. A supervisor can also coach the agent to improve call handling.

This feature is available with Service Cloud Voice using Amazon Connect, Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect, or Partner Telephony.
title: Viewing Sentiments of a Call Conversation in Service Cloud
